  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "Given an array AAA of integers of size NNN. For every window size from 111 to NNN, you have to find the maximum value among the minimum(s) of that window size in the array.\n\nFor example if A=[2,4,6]A = [2,4,6]A=[2,4,6] then\n\nWindows of size 111 are - [2],[4],[6][2], [4], [6][2],[4],[6], and the minimum value in each window is 2,4,62,4,62,4,6. Among these values, the maximum is 666.\n\nSimilarly, windows of size 222 are - [2,4],[4,6][2,4], [4,6][2,4],[4,6], and the minimum value in each window is 2,42,42,4. Among these values, the maximum is 444.\n\nSimilarly, Windows of size 333 are - [2,4,6][2,4,6][2,4,6], the minimum value in each window is 222. Among these values, the maximum is 222.\n\nSo the answer for this array will be [6,4,2][6,4,2][6,4,2].\n\n\nInput Format\n\nFirst-line will contain TTT, the number of test cases. Then the test cases follow.\nEach test case contains two lines of input.\nThe first line of every test case contains an integer NNN - the number of days\nThe second line of every test case contains NNN integers - A1,A2,..,AN A_1,A_2,..,A_NA1\u200b,A2\u200b,..,AN\u200b denoting the integers in the array.\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output in a single line NNN integers- the iii-th integer denotes the answer for the window of size iii.",
    "constraints": [
      "1\u2264T\u226415001 \\leq T \\leq 15001\u2264T\u22641500",
      "2\u2264N\u22642\u22c51052 \\leq N \\leq 2 \\cdot 10^52\u2264N\u22642\u22c5105",
      "1\u2264Ai\u22641091 \\leq A_i \\leq 10^91\u2264Ai\u200b\u2264109",
